==Countryside==
===Remnants of crops===
:''(from Deuteronomy 24:19-22 and Deuteronomy 23:24-25)''

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|1}} When thou cuttest down thine harvest in thy field, and hast forgot a sheaf in the field, thou shalt not go again to fetch it:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|2}} It shall be for the stranger, for the fatherless, and for the widow:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|3}} That the LORD thy God may bless thee in all the work of thine hands.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|4}} When thou beatest thine olive tree, thou shalt not go over the boughs again:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|5}} It shall be for the stranger, for the fatherless, and for the widow.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|6}} When thou gatherest the grapes of thy vineyard, thou shalt not glean it afterward:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|7}} It shall be for the stranger, for the fatherless, and for the widow.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|8}} And thou shalt remember that thou wast a bondman in the land of Egypt: therefore I command thee to do this thing.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|9}} When thou comest into thy neighbour's vineyard, then thou mayest eat grapes thy fill at thine own pleasure;

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|10}} But thou shalt not put any in thy vessel.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|11}} When thou comest into the standing corn of thy neighbour, then thou mayest pluck the ears with thine hand;

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|12}} But thou shalt not move a sickle unto thy neighbour's standing corn.

===Tithe===
:''(from Deuteronomy 14:22-29)''

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|1}} Thou shalt truly tithe all the increase of thy seed, that the field bringeth forth year by year.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|2}} And thou shalt eat before the LORD thy God, in the place which he shall choose to place his name there,

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|3}} The tithe of thy corn, of thy wine, and of thine oil, and the firstlings of thy herds and of thy flocks;

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|4}} That thou mayest learn to fear the LORD thy God always.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|5}} And if the way be too long for thee, so that thou art not able to carry it;

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|6}} Or if the place be too far from thee, which the LORD thy God shall choose to set his name there, when the LORD thy God hath blessed thee:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|7}} Then shalt thou turn it into money, and bind up the money in thine hand, and shalt go unto the place which the LORD thy God shall choose:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|8}} And thou shalt bestow that money for whatsoever thy soul lusteth after,

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|9}} For oxen, or for sheep, or for wine, or for strong drink, or for whatsoever thy soul desireth:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|10}} And thou shalt eat there before the LORD thy God, and thou shalt rejoice, thou, and thine household,

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|11}} And the Levite that is within thy gates; thou shalt not forsake him; for he hath no part nor inheritance with thee.

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|12}} At the end of three years thou shalt bring forth all the tithe of thine increase the same year, and shalt lay it up within thy gates:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|13}} And the Levite, (because he hath no part nor inheritance with thee,) and the stranger, and the fatherless, and the widow,

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|14}} Which are within thy gates, shall come, and shall eat and be satisfied;

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|15}} That the LORD thy God may bless thee in all the work of thine hand which thou doest.

===Birds nests===
:''(from Deuteronomy 22:6-7)''

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|1}} If a bird's nest chance to be before thee in the way in any tree, or on the ground, whether they be young ones, or eggs,

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|2}} And the dam sitting upon the young, or upon the eggs, thou shalt not take the dam with the young:

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|3}} But thou shalt in any wise let the dam go, and take the young to thee;

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|4}} That it may be well with thee, and that thou mayest prolong thy days.

===Oxen===
:''(from Deuteronomy 25:4)''

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|1}} Thou shalt not muzzle the ox when he treadeth out the corn

===Corpses===
:''(from Deuteronomy 14:21a)''

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|1}} Ye shall not eat of anything that dieth of itself: thou shalt give it unto the stranger that is in thy gates, that he may eat it;

{{font|size=smaller|color=#0000FF|2}} Or thou mayest sell it unto an alien: for thou art an holy people unto the LORD thy God.

